text: Darke County is a county in the U.S. state of Ohio. As of the 2020 census, the population was 51,881. Its county seat is Greenville. The county was created in 1809. It is named for William Darke, an officer in the American Revolutionary War. ==References== Category:1810s establishments in Ohio Category:1817 establishments in Ohio Category:Ohio counties
title: Darke County, Ohio
